[[File:Gaspard van Eyck - Seascape - WGA07585.jpg|thumb|right|300px|''Seascape'', ca. 1650, now in the Prado]]
'''Gaspar''' or '''Casper van Eyck''' (bapt. 6 February 1613 in [[Antwerp]] – bef. December 1674 in [[Brussels]]),<ref name=rkd>[https://rkd.nl/en/explore/artists/26952 Eyck, Casper van] at the [[RKD]]</ref> was a Flemish painter of marine subjects and sea-fights.

Van Eyck was received into the [[Guild of Saint Luke|Guild of St. Luke]] in 1632. He traveled to [[Genova]], where he collaborated with [[Cornelis de Wael]]. From 1656 until his death he worked in Brussels.<ref name=rkd/> Three pictures by him are in the [[Museo del Prado|Madrid Gallery]].  He painted various types of ships, including Turkish galleys with Turkish figures on them, and was still painting in Antwerp in 1660.<ref>[[Het Gulden Cabinet]], p. 367, 1660, [[Cornelis de Bie]]</ref>

